{{!--
  core-tricks-grid.hbs — compact symbolic-object grid for the twelve
  foundational atoms (toe-stall / clipper / mirage / legover / pickup /
  illusion / whirl / butterfly / swirl / osis / around-the-world / orbit).

  One partial shared by the landing page and glossary §10 so both surfaces
  share the same grid markup and stay in sync without duplication.

  Required `tricks` shape: FreestyleCoreTrickCard[] from freestyleService.
  Each entry: slug, semanticEquivalences[], symbolicNotation, addNumeric,
  addPending. Equivalences render as `≡` readings; notation as a small
  string under #slug; ADD as a numeric value or em-dash for pending rows.

  Caller controls scope (landing carries the section heading + footnote;
  glossary §10 carries its own h2). This partial renders only the grid markup.

  `idPrefix` controls the article's id attribute (default `core-trick-`):
    - landing surface passes `core-trick-` (matches #core-trick-X anchors)
    - glossary §10 passes `term-` (preserves the cross-page deep-link contract
      used by glossaryAnchors.ts and semantic-notation links)
--}}
<div class="freestyle-core-trick-grid">
  {{#each tricks}}
  <article class="core-trick-object" id="{{#if ../idPrefix}}{{../idPrefix}}{{else}}core-trick-{{/if}}{{slug}}">
    <p class="core-trick-slug">#{{displaySlug}}</p>
    {{#each semanticEquivalences}}
    <p class="core-trick-equivalence"><span class="core-trick-equiv-sigil">&equiv;</span> {{this}}</p>
    {{/each}}
    {{#if symbolicNotation}}
    <p class="core-trick-notation">{{symbolicNotation}}</p>
    {{/if}}
    {{#if addPending}}
    <p class="core-trick-add core-trick-add-pending" aria-label="ADD value pending">&mdash;</p>
    {{else}}
    <p class="core-trick-add"><span class="core-trick-add-value">{{addNumeric}}</span></p>
    {{/if}}
  </article>
  {{/each}}
</div>
